          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-jeff-rooker" title="Mr Jeff Rooker">Lord Rooker</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            My noble friend Lord Macdonald has looked into the issue. The vast majority of all those so-called regulations were minor&#x2014;for example, to close a road for repair. It is an absolute myth that there are loads of regulations. Some are necessary&#x2014;as they were under the previous government&#x2014;for road safety purposes. The vast majority, as I understand it&#x2014;I remember reading the Parliamentary Answer at the time&#x2014;were road closure orders required for necessary repairs to be carried out.</p><p>
            So it is an absolute myth that thousands of regulations are placed on thousands of local government officers every day. It is not true.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0648P0-05590'>
        <a name='S5LV0648P0_20030604_GCR_174'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-paul-white' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0648P0_20030604_GCR_174' title='Link to this speech by Mr Paul White' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
