            Before giving any of these less typical bodies full access to the freedoms of prudential borrowing, we must, in particular, be satisfied that they can cope
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_230gc' title='Col. 230GC &mdash; HL Deb 04 June 2003 vol 648 c230GC' name='column_230gc' href='#column_230gc' rel='bookmark'>230GC</a>
